89/* Add a CONF_VALUE name value pair to stack */
90
91int X509V3_add_value(const char *name, const char *value,
92 STACK_OF(CONF_VALUE) **extlist)
93{
94 CONF_VALUE *vtmp = NULL;
95 char *tname = NULL, *tvalue = NULL;
96 if (name && !(tname = OPENSSL_strdup(name)))
97 goto err;
98 if (value && !(tvalue = OPENSSL_strdup(value)))
99 goto err;
100 if (!(vtmp = CONF_VALUE_new()))
101 goto err;
102 if (!*extlist && !(*extlist = sk_CONF_VALUE_new_null()))
103 goto err;
104 vtmp->section = NULL;
105 vtmp->name = tname;
106 vtmp->value = tvalue;
107 if (!sk_CONF_VALUE_push(*extlist, vtmp))
108 goto err;
109 return 1;
110 err:
111 OPENSSL_PUT_ERROR(X509V3, ERR_R_MALLOC_FAILURE);
112 if (vtmp)
113 OPENSSL_free(vtmp);
114 if (tname)
115 OPENSSL_free(tname);
116 if (tvalue)
117 OPENSSL_free(tvalue);
118 return 0;
119}

129void X509V3_conf_free(CONF_VALUE *conf)
130{
131 if (!conf)
132 return;
133 if (conf->name)
134 OPENSSL_free(conf->name);
135 if (conf->value)
136 OPENSSL_free(conf->value);
137 if (conf->section)
138 OPENSSL_free(conf->section);
139 OPENSSL_free(conf);
140}

158static char *bignum_to_string(const BIGNUM *bn)
159{
160 char *tmp, *ret;
161 size_t len;
162
163 /*
164 * Display large numbers in hex and small numbers in decimal. Converting to
165 * decimal takes quadratic time and is no more useful than hex for large
166 * numbers.
167 */
168 if (BN_num_bits(bn) < 32) {
169 return BN_bn2dec(bn);
170 }
171
172 tmp = BN_bn2hex(bn);
173 if (tmp == NULL) {
174 return NULL;
175 }
176
177 len = strlen(tmp) + 3;
178 ret = OPENSSL_malloc(len);
179 if (ret == NULL) {
180 OPENSSL_PUT_ERROR(X509V3, ERR_R_MALLOC_FAILURE);
181 OPENSSL_free(tmp);
182 return NULL;
183 }
184
185 /* Prepend "0x", but place it after the "-" if negative. */
186 if (tmp[0] == '-') {
187 OPENSSL_strlcpy(ret, "-0x", len);
188 OPENSSL_strlcat(ret, tmp + 1, len);
189 } else {
190 OPENSSL_strlcpy(ret, "0x", len);
191 OPENSSL_strlcat(ret, tmp, len);
192 }
193 OPENSSL_free(tmp);
194 return ret;
195}

197char *i2s_ASN1_ENUMERATED(X509V3_EXT_METHOD *method, const ASN1_ENUMERATED *a)
198{
199 BIGNUM *bntmp = NULL;
200 char *strtmp = NULL;
201 if (!a)
202 return NULL;
203 if (!(bntmp = ASN1_ENUMERATED_to_BN(a, NULL)) ||
204 !(strtmp = bignum_to_string(bntmp)))
205 OPENSSL_PUT_ERROR(X509V3, ERR_R_MALLOC_FAILURE);
206 BN_free(bntmp);
207 return strtmp;
208}

210char *i2s_ASN1_INTEGER(X509V3_EXT_METHOD *method, const ASN1_INTEGER *a)
211{
212 BIGNUM *bntmp = NULL;
213 char *strtmp = NULL;
214 if (!a)
215 return NULL;
216 if (!(bntmp = ASN1_INTEGER_to_BN(a, NULL)) ||
217 !(strtmp = bignum_to_string(bntmp)))
218 OPENSSL_PUT_ERROR(X509V3, ERR_R_MALLOC_FAILURE);
219 BN_free(bntmp);
220 return strtmp;
221}
222
223ASN1_INTEGER *s2i_ASN1_INTEGER(X509V3_EXT_METHOD *method, const char *value)
224{
225 BIGNUM *bn = NULL;
226 ASN1_INTEGER *aint;
227 int isneg, ishex;
228 int ret;
229 if (!value) {
230 OPENSSL_PUT_ERROR(X509V3, X509V3_R_INVALID_NULL_VALUE);
231 return 0;
232 }
233 bn = BN_new();
234 if (value[0] == '-') {
235 value++;
236 isneg = 1;
237 } else
238 isneg = 0;
239
240 if (value[0] == '0' && ((value[1] == 'x') || (value[1] == 'X'))) {
241 value += 2;
242 ishex = 1;
243 } else
244 ishex = 0;
245
246 if (ishex)
247 ret = BN_hex2bn(&bn, value);
248 else
249 ret = BN_dec2bn(&bn, value);
250
251 if (!ret || value[ret]) {
252 BN_free(bn);
253 OPENSSL_PUT_ERROR(X509V3, X509V3_R_BN_DEC2BN_ERROR);
254 return 0;
255 }
256
257 if (isneg && BN_is_zero(bn))
258 isneg = 0;
259
260 aint = BN_to_ASN1_INTEGER(bn, NULL);
261 BN_free(bn);
262 if (!aint) {
263 OPENSSL_PUT_ERROR(X509V3, X509V3_R_BN_TO_ASN1_INTEGER_ERROR);
264 return 0;
265 }
266 if (isneg)
267 aint->type |= V_ASN1_NEG;
268 return aint;
269}

271int X509V3_add_value_int(const char *name, ASN1_INTEGER *aint,
272 STACK_OF(CONF_VALUE) **extlist)
273{
274 char *strtmp;
275 int ret;
276 if (!aint)
277 return 1;
278 if (!(strtmp = i2s_ASN1_INTEGER(NULL, aint)))
279 return 0;
280 ret = X509V3_add_value(name, strtmp, extlist);
281 OPENSSL_free(strtmp);
282 return ret;
283}

285int X509V3_get_value_bool(const CONF_VALUE *value, int *asn1_bool)
286{
287 char *btmp;
288 if (!(btmp = value->value))
289 goto err;
290 if (!strcmp(btmp, "TRUE") || !strcmp(btmp, "true")
291 || !strcmp(btmp, "Y") || !strcmp(btmp, "y")
292 || !strcmp(btmp, "YES") || !strcmp(btmp, "yes")) {
293 *asn1_bool = 0xff;
294 return 1;
295 } else if (!strcmp(btmp, "FALSE") || !strcmp(btmp, "false")
296 || !strcmp(btmp, "N") || !strcmp(btmp, "n")
297 || !strcmp(btmp, "NO") || !strcmp(btmp, "no")) {
298 *asn1_bool = 0;
299 return 1;
300 }
301 err:
302 OPENSSL_PUT_ERROR(X509V3, X509V3_R_INVALID_BOOLEAN_STRING);
303 X509V3_conf_err(value);
304 return 0;
305}
306
307int X509V3_get_value_int(const CONF_VALUE *value, ASN1_INTEGER **aint)
308{
309 ASN1_INTEGER *itmp;
310 if (!(itmp = s2i_ASN1_INTEGER(NULL, value->value))) {
311 X509V3_conf_err(value);
312 return 0;
313 }
314 *aint = itmp;
315 return 1;
316}

318#define HDR_NAME 1
319#define HDR_VALUE 2
320
321/*
322 * #define DEBUG
323 */
324
325STACK_OF(CONF_VALUE) *X509V3_parse_list(const char *line)
326{
327 char *p, *q, c;
328 char *ntmp, *vtmp;
329 STACK_OF(CONF_VALUE) *values = NULL;
330 char *linebuf;
331 int state;
332 /* We are going to modify the line so copy it first */
333 linebuf = OPENSSL_strdup(line);
334 if (linebuf == NULL) {
335 OPENSSL_PUT_ERROR(X509V3, ERR_R_MALLOC_FAILURE);
336 goto err;
337 }
338 state = HDR_NAME;
339 ntmp = NULL;
340 /* Go through all characters */
341 for (p = linebuf, q = linebuf; (c = *p) && (c != '\r') && (c != '\n');
342 p++) {
343
344 switch (state) {
345 case HDR_NAME:
346 if (c == ':') {
347 state = HDR_VALUE;
348 *p = 0;
349 ntmp = strip_spaces(q);
350 if (!ntmp) {
351 OPENSSL_PUT_ERROR(X509V3, X509V3_R_INVALID_NULL_NAME);
352 goto err;
353 }
354 q = p + 1;
355 } else if (c == ',') {
356 *p = 0;
357 ntmp = strip_spaces(q);
358 q = p + 1;
359#if 0
360 printf("%s\n", ntmp);
361#endif
362 if (!ntmp) {
363 OPENSSL_PUT_ERROR(X509V3, X509V3_R_INVALID_NULL_NAME);
364 goto err;
365 }
366 X509V3_add_value(ntmp, NULL, &values);
367 }
368 break;
369
370 case HDR_VALUE:
371 if (c == ',') {
372 state = HDR_NAME;
373 *p = 0;
374 vtmp = strip_spaces(q);
375#if 0
376 printf("%s\n", ntmp);
377#endif
378 if (!vtmp) {
379 OPENSSL_PUT_ERROR(X509V3, X509V3_R_INVALID_NULL_VALUE);
380 goto err;
381 }
382 X509V3_add_value(ntmp, vtmp, &values);
383 ntmp = NULL;
384 q = p + 1;
385 }
386
387 }
388 }
389
390 if (state == HDR_VALUE) {
391 vtmp = strip_spaces(q);
392#if 0
393 printf("%s=%s\n", ntmp, vtmp);
394#endif
395 if (!vtmp) {
396 OPENSSL_PUT_ERROR(X509V3, X509V3_R_INVALID_NULL_VALUE);
397 goto err;
398 }
399 X509V3_add_value(ntmp, vtmp, &values);
400 } else {
401 ntmp = strip_spaces(q);
402#if 0
403 printf("%s\n", ntmp);
404#endif
405 if (!ntmp) {
406 OPENSSL_PUT_ERROR(X509V3, X509V3_R_INVALID_NULL_NAME);
407 goto err;
408 }
409 X509V3_add_value(ntmp, NULL, &values);
410 }
411 OPENSSL_free(linebuf);
412 return values;
413
414 err:
415 OPENSSL_free(linebuf);
416 sk_CONF_VALUE_pop_free(values, X509V3_conf_free);
417 return NULL;
418
419}
420
421/* Delete leading and trailing spaces from a string */
422static char *strip_spaces(char *name)
423{
424 char *p, *q;
425 /* Skip over leading spaces */
426 p = name;
427 while (*p && isspace((unsigned char)*p))
428 p++;
429 if (!*p)
430 return NULL;
431 q = p + strlen(p) - 1;
432 while ((q != p) && isspace((unsigned char)*q))
433 q--;
434 if (p != q)
435 q[1] = 0;
436 if (!*p)
437 return NULL;
438 return p;
439}

441/* hex string utilities */
442
443/*
444 * Given a buffer of length 'len' return a OPENSSL_malloc'ed string with its
445 * hex representation @@@ (Contents of buffer are always kept in ASCII, also
446 * on EBCDIC machines)
447 */
448
449char *x509v3_bytes_to_hex(const unsigned char *buffer, long len)
450{
451 char *tmp, *q;
452 const unsigned char *p;
453 int i;
454 static const char hexdig[] = "0123456789ABCDEF";
455 if (!buffer || !len)
456 return NULL;
457 if (!(tmp = OPENSSL_malloc(len * 3 + 1))) {
458 OPENSSL_PUT_ERROR(X509V3, ERR_R_MALLOC_FAILURE);
459 return NULL;
460 }
461 q = tmp;
462 for (i = 0, p = buffer; i < len; i++, p++) {
463 *q++ = hexdig[(*p >> 4) & 0xf];
464 *q++ = hexdig[*p & 0xf];
465 *q++ = ':';
466 }
467 q[-1] = 0;
468
469 return tmp;
470}
471
472unsigned char *x509v3_hex_to_bytes(const char *str, long *len)
473{
474 unsigned char *hexbuf, *q;
475 unsigned char ch, cl, *p;
476 if (!str) {
477 OPENSSL_PUT_ERROR(X509V3, X509V3_R_INVALID_NULL_ARGUMENT);
478 return NULL;
479 }
480 if (!(hexbuf = OPENSSL_malloc(strlen(str) >> 1)))
481 goto err;
482 for (p = (unsigned char *)str, q = hexbuf; *p;) {
483 ch = *p++;
484 if (ch == ':')
485 continue;
486 cl = *p++;
487 if (!cl) {
488 OPENSSL_PUT_ERROR(X509V3, X509V3_R_ODD_NUMBER_OF_DIGITS);
489 OPENSSL_free(hexbuf);
490 return NULL;
491 }
492
493 if ((ch >= '0') && (ch <= '9'))
494 ch -= '0';
495 else if ((ch >= 'a') && (ch <= 'f'))
496 ch -= 'a' - 10;
497 else if ((ch >= 'A') && (ch <= 'F'))
498 ch -= 'A' - 10;
499 else
500 goto badhex;
501
502 if ((cl >= '0') && (cl <= '9'))
503 cl -= '0';
504 else if ((cl >= 'a') && (cl <= 'f'))
505 cl -= 'a' - 10;
506 else if ((cl >= 'A') && (cl <= 'F'))
507 cl -= 'A' - 10;
508 else
509 goto badhex;
510
511 *q++ = (ch << 4) | cl;
512 }
513
514 if (len)
515 *len = q - hexbuf;
516
517 return hexbuf;
518
519 err:
520 if (hexbuf)
521 OPENSSL_free(hexbuf);
522 OPENSSL_PUT_ERROR(X509V3, ERR_R_MALLOC_FAILURE);
523 return NULL;
524
525 badhex:
526 OPENSSL_free(hexbuf);
527 OPENSSL_PUT_ERROR(X509V3, X509V3_R_ILLEGAL_HEX_DIGIT);
528 return NULL;
529
530}

532int x509v3_name_cmp(const char *name, const char *cmp)
533{
534 int len, ret;
535 char c;
536 len = strlen(cmp);
537 if ((ret = strncmp(name, cmp, len)))
538 return ret;
539 c = name[len];
540 if (!c || (c == '.'))
541 return 0;
542 return 1;
543}

550STACK_OF(OPENSSL_STRING) *X509_get1_email(X509 *x)
551{
552 GENERAL_NAMES *gens;
553 STACK_OF(OPENSSL_STRING) *ret;
554
555 gens = X509_get_ext_d2i(x, NID_subject_alt_name, NULL, NULL);
556 ret = get_email(X509_get_subject_name(x), gens);
557 sk_GENERAL_NAME_pop_free(gens, GENERAL_NAME_free);
558 return ret;
559}
560
561STACK_OF(OPENSSL_STRING) *X509_get1_ocsp(X509 *x)
562{
563 AUTHORITY_INFO_ACCESS *info;
564 STACK_OF(OPENSSL_STRING) *ret = NULL;
565 size_t i;
566
567 info = X509_get_ext_d2i(x, NID_info_access, NULL, NULL);
568 if (!info)
569 return NULL;
570 for (i = 0; i < sk_ACCESS_DESCRIPTION_num(info); i++) {
571 ACCESS_DESCRIPTION *ad = sk_ACCESS_DESCRIPTION_value(info, i);
572 if (OBJ_obj2nid(ad->method) == NID_ad_OCSP) {
573 if (ad->location->type == GEN_URI) {
574 if (!append_ia5
575 (&ret, ad->location->d.uniformResourceIdentifier))
576 break;
577 }
578 }
579 }
580 AUTHORITY_INFO_ACCESS_free(info);
581 return ret;
582}

584STACK_OF(OPENSSL_STRING) *X509_REQ_get1_email(X509_REQ *x)
585{
586 GENERAL_NAMES *gens;
587 STACK_OF(X509_EXTENSION) *exts;
588 STACK_OF(OPENSSL_STRING) *ret;
589
590 exts = X509_REQ_get_extensions(x);
591 gens = X509V3_get_d2i(exts, NID_subject_alt_name, NULL, NULL);
592 ret = get_email(X509_REQ_get_subject_name(x), gens);
593 sk_GENERAL_NAME_pop_free(gens, GENERAL_NAME_free);
594 sk_X509_EXTENSION_pop_free(exts, X509_EXTENSION_free);
595 return ret;
596}
597
598static STACK_OF(OPENSSL_STRING) *get_email(X509_NAME *name,
599 GENERAL_NAMES *gens)
600{
601 STACK_OF(OPENSSL_STRING) *ret = NULL;
602 X509_NAME_ENTRY *ne;
603 ASN1_IA5STRING *email;
604 GENERAL_NAME *gen;
605 int i;
606 size_t j;
607 /* Now add any email address(es) to STACK */
608 i = -1;
609 /* First supplied X509_NAME */
610 while ((i = X509_NAME_get_index_by_NID(name,
611 NID_pkcs9_emailAddress, i)) >= 0) {
612 ne = X509_NAME_get_entry(name, i);
613 email = X509_NAME_ENTRY_get_data(ne);
614 if (!append_ia5(&ret, email))
615 return NULL;
616 }
617 for (j = 0; j < sk_GENERAL_NAME_num(gens); j++) {
618 gen = sk_GENERAL_NAME_value(gens, j);
619 if (gen->type != GEN_EMAIL)
620 continue;
621 if (!append_ia5(&ret, gen->d.ia5))
622 return NULL;
623 }
624 return ret;
625}

629 OPENSSL_free(str);

631
632static int append_ia5(STACK_OF(OPENSSL_STRING) **sk, ASN1_IA5STRING *email)
633{
634 char *emtmp;
635 /* First some sanity checks */
636 if (email->type != V_ASN1_IA5STRING)
637 return 1;
638 if (!email->data || !email->length)
639 return 1;
640 if (!*sk)
641 *sk = sk_OPENSSL_STRING_new(sk_strcmp);
642 if (!*sk)
643 return 0;
644 /* Don't add duplicates */
645 sk_OPENSSL_STRING_sort(*sk);
646 if (sk_OPENSSL_STRING_find(*sk, NULL, (char *)email->data))
647 return 1;
648 emtmp = OPENSSL_strdup((char *)email->data);
649 if (!emtmp || !sk_OPENSSL_STRING_push(*sk, emtmp)) {
650 X509_email_free(*sk);
651 *sk = NULL;
652 return 0;
653 }
654 return 1;
655}
656
657void X509_email_free(STACK_OF(OPENSSL_STRING) *sk)
658{
659 sk_OPENSSL_STRING_pop_free(sk, str_free);
660}

662typedef int (*equal_fn) (const unsigned char *pattern, size_t pattern_len,
663 const unsigned char *subject, size_t subject_len,
664 unsigned int flags);
665
666/* Skip pattern prefix to match "wildcard" subject */
667static void skip_prefix(const unsigned char **p, size_t *plen,
668 const unsigned char *subject, size_t subject_len,
669 unsigned int flags)
670{
671 const unsigned char *pattern = *p;
672 size_t pattern_len = *plen;
673
674 /*
675 * If subject starts with a leading '.' followed by more octets, and
676 * pattern is longer, compare just an equal-length suffix with the
677 * full subject (starting at the '.'), provided the prefix contains
678 * no NULs.
679 */
680 if ((flags & _X509_CHECK_FLAG_DOT_SUBDOMAINS) == 0)
681 return;
682
683 while (pattern_len > subject_len && *pattern) {
684 if ((flags & X509_CHECK_FLAG_SINGLE_LABEL_SUBDOMAINS) &&
685 *pattern == '.')
686 break;
687 ++pattern;
688 --pattern_len;
689 }
690
691 /* Skip if entire prefix acceptable */
692 if (pattern_len == subject_len) {
693 *p = pattern;
694 *plen = pattern_len;
695 }
696}
697
698/* Compare while ASCII ignoring case. */
699static int equal_nocase(const unsigned char *pattern, size_t pattern_len,
700 const unsigned char *subject, size_t subject_len,
701 unsigned int flags)
702{
703 skip_prefix(&pattern, &pattern_len, subject, subject_len, flags);
704 if (pattern_len != subject_len)
705 return 0;
706 while (pattern_len) {
707 unsigned char l = *pattern;
708 unsigned char r = *subject;
709 /* The pattern must not contain NUL characters. */
710 if (l == 0)
711 return 0;
712 if (l != r) {
713 if ('A' <= l && l <= 'Z')
714 l = (l - 'A') + 'a';
715 if ('A' <= r && r <= 'Z')
716 r = (r - 'A') + 'a';
717 if (l != r)
718 return 0;
719 }
720 ++pattern;
721 ++subject;
722 --pattern_len;
723 }
724 return 1;
725}
726
727/* Compare using OPENSSL_memcmp. */
728static int equal_case(const unsigned char *pattern, size_t pattern_len,
729 const unsigned char *subject, size_t subject_len,
730 unsigned int flags)
731{
732 skip_prefix(&pattern, &pattern_len, subject, subject_len, flags);
733 if (pattern_len != subject_len)
734 return 0;
735 return !OPENSSL_memcmp(pattern, subject, pattern_len);
736}
737
738/*
739 * RFC 5280, section 7.5, requires that only the domain is compared in a
740 * case-insensitive manner.
741 */
742static int equal_email(const unsigned char *a, size_t a_len,
743 const unsigned char *b, size_t b_len,
744 unsigned int unused_flags)
745{
746 size_t i = a_len;
747 if (a_len != b_len)
748 return 0;
749 /*
750 * We search backwards for the '@' character, so that we do not have to
751 * deal with quoted local-parts. The domain part is compared in a
752 * case-insensitive manner.
753 */
754 while (i > 0) {
755 --i;
756 if (a[i] == '@' || b[i] == '@') {
757 if (!equal_nocase(a + i, a_len - i, b + i, a_len - i, 0))
758 return 0;
759 break;
760 }
761 }
762 if (i == 0)
763 i = a_len;
764 return equal_case(a, i, b, i, 0);
765}
766
767/*
768 * Compare the prefix and suffix with the subject, and check that the
769 * characters in-between are valid.
770 */
771static int wildcard_match(const unsigned char *prefix, size_t prefix_len,
772 const unsigned char *suffix, size_t suffix_len,
773 const unsigned char *subject, size_t subject_len,
774 unsigned int flags)
775{
776 const unsigned char *wildcard_start;
777 const unsigned char *wildcard_end;
778 const unsigned char *p;
779 int allow_multi = 0;
780 int allow_idna = 0;
781
782 if (subject_len < prefix_len + suffix_len)
783 return 0;
784 if (!equal_nocase(prefix, prefix_len, subject, prefix_len, flags))
785 return 0;
786 wildcard_start = subject + prefix_len;
787 wildcard_end = subject + (subject_len - suffix_len);
788 if (!equal_nocase(wildcard_end, suffix_len, suffix, suffix_len, flags))
789 return 0;
790 /*
791 * If the wildcard makes up the entire first label, it must match at
792 * least one character.
793 */
794 if (prefix_len == 0 && *suffix == '.') {
795 if (wildcard_start == wildcard_end)
796 return 0;
797 allow_idna = 1;
798 if (flags & X509_CHECK_FLAG_MULTI_LABEL_WILDCARDS)
799 allow_multi = 1;
800 }
801 /* IDNA labels cannot match partial wildcards */
802 if (!allow_idna &&
803 subject_len >= 4
804 && OPENSSL_strncasecmp((char *)subject, "xn--", 4) == 0)
805 return 0;
806 /* The wildcard may match a literal '*' */
807 if (wildcard_end == wildcard_start + 1 && *wildcard_start == '*')
808 return 1;
809 /*
810 * Check that the part matched by the wildcard contains only
811 * permitted characters and only matches a single label unless
812 * allow_multi is set.
813 */
814 for (p = wildcard_start; p != wildcard_end; ++p)
815 if (!(('0' <= *p && *p <= '9') ||
816 ('A' <= *p && *p <= 'Z') ||
817 ('a' <= *p && *p <= 'z') ||
818 *p == '-' || (allow_multi && *p == '.')))
819 return 0;
820 return 1;
821}
822
823#define LABEL_START (1 << 0)
824#define LABEL_END (1 << 1)
825#define LABEL_HYPHEN (1 << 2)
826#define LABEL_IDNA (1 << 3)
827
828static const unsigned char *valid_star(const unsigned char *p, size_t len,
829 unsigned int flags)
830{
831 const unsigned char *star = 0;
832 size_t i;
833 int state = LABEL_START;
834 int dots = 0;
835 for (i = 0; i < len; ++i) {
836 /*
837 * Locate first and only legal wildcard, either at the start
838 * or end of a non-IDNA first and not final label.
839 */
840 if (p[i] == '*') {
841 int atstart = (state & LABEL_START);
842 int atend = (i == len - 1 || p[i + 1] == '.');
843 /*
844 * At most one wildcard per pattern.
845 * No wildcards in IDNA labels.
846 * No wildcards after the first label.
847 */
848 if (star != NULL || (state & LABEL_IDNA) != 0 || dots)
849 return NULL;
850 /* Only full-label '*.example.com' wildcards? */
851 if ((flags & X509_CHECK_FLAG_NO_PARTIAL_WILDCARDS)
852 && (!atstart || !atend))
853 return NULL;
854 /* No 'foo*bar' wildcards */
855 if (!atstart && !atend)
856 return NULL;
857 star = &p[i];
858 state &= ~LABEL_START;
859 } else if (('a' <= p[i] && p[i] <= 'z')
860 || ('A' <= p[i] && p[i] <= 'Z')
861 || ('0' <= p[i] && p[i] <= '9')) {
862 if ((state & LABEL_START) != 0
863 && len - i >= 4
864 && OPENSSL_strncasecmp((char *)&p[i], "xn--", 4) == 0)
865 state |= LABEL_IDNA;
866 state &= ~(LABEL_HYPHEN | LABEL_START);
867 } else if (p[i] == '.') {
868 if ((state & (LABEL_HYPHEN | LABEL_START)) != 0)
869 return NULL;
870 state = LABEL_START;
871 ++dots;
872 } else if (p[i] == '-') {
873 /* no domain/subdomain starts with '-' */
874 if ((state & LABEL_START) != 0)
875 return NULL;
876 state |= LABEL_HYPHEN;
877 } else
878 return NULL;
879 }
880
881 /*
882 * The final label must not end in a hyphen or ".", and
883 * there must be at least two dots after the star.
884 */
885 if ((state & (LABEL_START | LABEL_HYPHEN)) != 0 || dots < 2)
886 return NULL;
887 return star;
888}
889
890/* Compare using wildcards. */
891static int equal_wildcard(const unsigned char *pattern, size_t pattern_len,
892 const unsigned char *subject, size_t subject_len,
893 unsigned int flags)
894{
895 const unsigned char *star = NULL;
896
897 /*
898 * Subject names starting with '.' can only match a wildcard pattern
899 * via a subject sub-domain pattern suffix match.
900 */
901 if (!(subject_len > 1 && subject[0] == '.'))
902 star = valid_star(pattern, pattern_len, flags);
903 if (star == NULL)
904 return equal_nocase(pattern, pattern_len,
905 subject, subject_len, flags);
906 return wildcard_match(pattern, star - pattern,
907 star + 1, (pattern + pattern_len) - star - 1,
908 subject, subject_len, flags);
909}
910
911int x509v3_looks_like_dns_name(const unsigned char *in, size_t len) {
912 /* This function is used as a heuristic for whether a common name is a
913 * hostname to be matched, or merely a decorative name to describe the
914 * subject. This heuristic must be applied to both name constraints and the
915 * common name fallback, so it must be loose enough to accept hostname
916 * common names, and tight enough to reject decorative common names. */
917
918 if (len > 0 && in[len - 1] == '.') {
919 len--;
920 }
921
922 /* Wildcards are allowed in front. */
923 if (len >= 2 && in[0] == '*' && in[1] == '.') {
924 in += 2;
925 len -= 2;
926 }
927
928 if (len == 0) {
929 return 0;
930 }
931
932 size_t label_start = 0;
933 for (size_t i = 0; i < len; i++) {
934 unsigned char c = in[i];
935 if ((c >= 'a' && c <= 'z') ||
936 (c >= '0' && c <= '9') ||
937 (c >= 'A' && c <= 'Z') ||
938 (c == '-' && i > label_start) ||
939 /* These are not valid characters in hostnames, but commonly found
940 * in deployments outside the Web PKI. */
941 c == '_' ||
942 c == ':') {
943 continue;
944 }
945
946 /* Labels must not be empty. */
947 if (c == '.' && i > label_start && i < len - 1) {
948 label_start = i + 1;
949 continue;
950 }
951
952 return 0;
953 }
954
955 return 1;
956}

958/*
959 * Compare an ASN1_STRING to a supplied string. If they match return 1. If
960 * cmp_type > 0 only compare if string matches the type, otherwise convert it
961 * to UTF8.
962 */
963
964static int do_check_string(ASN1_STRING *a, int cmp_type, equal_fn equal,
965 unsigned int flags, int check_type, const char *b,
966 size_t blen, char **peername)
967{
968 int rv = 0;
969
970 if (!a->data || !a->length)
971 return 0;
972 if (cmp_type > 0) {
973 if (cmp_type != a->type)
974 return 0;
975 if (cmp_type == V_ASN1_IA5STRING)
976 rv = equal(a->data, a->length, (unsigned char *)b, blen, flags);
977 else if (a->length == (int)blen && !OPENSSL_memcmp(a->data, b, blen))
978 rv = 1;
979 if (rv > 0 && peername)
980 *peername = OPENSSL_strndup((char *)a->data, a->length);
981 } else {
982 int astrlen;
983 unsigned char *astr;
984 astrlen = ASN1_STRING_to_UTF8(&astr, a);
985 if (astrlen < 0)
986 return -1;
987 /*
988 * We check the common name against DNS name constraints if it passes
989 * |x509v3_looks_like_dns_name|. Thus we must not consider common names
990 * for DNS fallbacks if they fail this check.
991 */
992 if (check_type == GEN_DNS &&
993 !x509v3_looks_like_dns_name(astr, astrlen)) {
994 rv = 0;
995 } else {
996 rv = equal(astr, astrlen, (unsigned char *)b, blen, flags);
997 }
998 if (rv > 0 && peername)
999 *peername = OPENSSL_strndup((char *)astr, astrlen);
1000 OPENSSL_free(astr);
1001 }
1002 return rv;
1003}
1004
1005static int do_x509_check(X509 *x, const char *chk, size_t chklen,
1006 unsigned int flags, int check_type, char **peername)
1007{
1008 GENERAL_NAMES *gens = NULL;
1009 X509_NAME *name = NULL;
1010 size_t i;
1011 int j;
1012 int cnid = NID_undef;
1013 int alt_type;
1014 int rv = 0;
1015 equal_fn equal;
1016
1017 /* See below, this flag is internal-only */
1018 flags &= ~_X509_CHECK_FLAG_DOT_SUBDOMAINS;
1019 if (check_type == GEN_EMAIL) {
1020 cnid = NID_pkcs9_emailAddress;
1021 alt_type = V_ASN1_IA5STRING;
1022 equal = equal_email;
1023 } else if (check_type == GEN_DNS) {
1024 cnid = NID_commonName;
1025 /* Implicit client-side DNS sub-domain pattern */
1026 if (chklen > 1 && chk[0] == '.')
1027 flags |= _X509_CHECK_FLAG_DOT_SUBDOMAINS;
1028 alt_type = V_ASN1_IA5STRING;
1029 if (flags & X509_CHECK_FLAG_NO_WILDCARDS)
1030 equal = equal_nocase;
1031 else
1032 equal = equal_wildcard;
1033 } else {
1034 alt_type = V_ASN1_OCTET_STRING;
1035 equal = equal_case;
1036 }
1037
1038 gens = X509_get_ext_d2i(x, NID_subject_alt_name, NULL, NULL);
1039 if (gens) {
1040 for (i = 0; i < sk_GENERAL_NAME_num(gens); i++) {
1041 GENERAL_NAME *gen;
1042 ASN1_STRING *cstr;
1043 gen = sk_GENERAL_NAME_value(gens, i);
1044 if (gen->type != check_type)
1045 continue;
1046 if (check_type == GEN_EMAIL)
1047 cstr = gen->d.rfc822Name;
1048 else if (check_type == GEN_DNS)
1049 cstr = gen->d.dNSName;
1050 else
1051 cstr = gen->d.iPAddress;
1052 /* Positive on success, negative on error! */
1053 if ((rv = do_check_string(cstr, alt_type, equal, flags, check_type,
1054 chk, chklen, peername)) != 0)
1055 break;
1056 }
1057 GENERAL_NAMES_free(gens);
1058 return rv;
1059 }
1060
1061 /* We're done if CN-ID is not pertinent */
1062 if (cnid == NID_undef || (flags & X509_CHECK_FLAG_NEVER_CHECK_SUBJECT))
1063 return 0;
1064
1065 j = -1;
1066 name = X509_get_subject_name(x);
1067 while ((j = X509_NAME_get_index_by_NID(name, cnid, j)) >= 0) {
1068 X509_NAME_ENTRY *ne;
1069 ASN1_STRING *str;
1070 ne = X509_NAME_get_entry(name, j);
1071 str = X509_NAME_ENTRY_get_data(ne);
1072 /* Positive on success, negative on error! */
1073 if ((rv = do_check_string(str, -1, equal, flags, check_type,
1074 chk, chklen, peername)) != 0)
1075 return rv;
1076 }
1077 return 0;
1078}

1121/*
1122 * Convert IP addresses both IPv4 and IPv6 into an OCTET STRING compatible
1123 * with RFC3280.
1124 */
1125
1126ASN1_OCTET_STRING *a2i_IPADDRESS(const char *ipasc)
1127{
1128 unsigned char ipout[16];
1129 ASN1_OCTET_STRING *ret;
1130 int iplen;
1131
1132 /* If string contains a ':' assume IPv6 */
1133
1134 iplen = a2i_ipadd(ipout, ipasc);
1135
1136 if (!iplen)
1137 return NULL;
1138
1139 ret = ASN1_OCTET_STRING_new();
1140 if (!ret)
1141 return NULL;
1142 if (!ASN1_OCTET_STRING_set(ret, ipout, iplen)) {
1143 ASN1_OCTET_STRING_free(ret);
1144 return NULL;
1145 }
1146 return ret;
1147}
1148
1149ASN1_OCTET_STRING *a2i_IPADDRESS_NC(const char *ipasc)
1150{
1151 ASN1_OCTET_STRING *ret = NULL;
1152 unsigned char ipout[32];
1153 char *iptmp = NULL, *p;
1154 int iplen1, iplen2;
1155 p = strchr(ipasc, '/');
1156 if (!p)
1157 return NULL;
1158 iptmp = OPENSSL_strdup(ipasc);
1159 if (!iptmp)
1160 return NULL;
1161 p = iptmp + (p - ipasc);
1162 *p++ = 0;
1163
1164 iplen1 = a2i_ipadd(ipout, iptmp);
1165
1166 if (!iplen1)
1167 goto err;
1168
1169 iplen2 = a2i_ipadd(ipout + iplen1, p);
1170
1171 OPENSSL_free(iptmp);
1172 iptmp = NULL;
1173
1174 if (!iplen2 || (iplen1 != iplen2))
1175 goto err;
1176
1177 ret = ASN1_OCTET_STRING_new();
1178 if (!ret)
1179 goto err;
1180 if (!ASN1_OCTET_STRING_set(ret, ipout, iplen1 + iplen2))
1181 goto err;
1182
1183 return ret;
1184
1185 err:
1186 if (iptmp)
1187 OPENSSL_free(iptmp);
1188 if (ret)
1189 ASN1_OCTET_STRING_free(ret);
1190 return NULL;
1191}
1192
1193int a2i_ipadd(unsigned char *ipout, const char *ipasc)
1194{
1195 /* If string contains a ':' assume IPv6 */
1196
1197 if (strchr(ipasc, ':')) {
1198 if (!ipv6_from_asc(ipout, ipasc))
1199 return 0;
1200 return 16;
1201 } else {
1202 if (!ipv4_from_asc(ipout, ipasc))
1203 return 0;
1204 return 4;
1205 }
1206}
1207
1208static int ipv4_from_asc(unsigned char *v4, const char *in)
1209{
1210 int a0, a1, a2, a3;
1211 if (sscanf(in, "%d.%d.%d.%d", &a0, &a1, &a2, &a3) != 4)
1212 return 0;
1213 if ((a0 < 0) || (a0 > 255) || (a1 < 0) || (a1 > 255)
1214 || (a2 < 0) || (a2 > 255) || (a3 < 0) || (a3 > 255))
1215 return 0;
1216 v4[0] = a0;
1217 v4[1] = a1;
1218 v4[2] = a2;
1219 v4[3] = a3;
1220 return 1;
1221}
1222
1223typedef struct {
1224 /* Temporary store for IPV6 output */
1225 unsigned char tmp[16];
1226 /* Total number of bytes in tmp */
1227 int total;
1228 /* The position of a zero (corresponding to '::') */
1229 int zero_pos;
1230 /* Number of zeroes */
1231 int zero_cnt;
1232} IPV6_STAT;
1233
1234static int ipv6_from_asc(unsigned char *v6, const char *in)
1235{
1236 IPV6_STAT v6stat;
1237 v6stat.total = 0;
1238 v6stat.zero_pos = -1;
1239 v6stat.zero_cnt = 0;
1240 /*
1241 * Treat the IPv6 representation as a list of values separated by ':'.
1242 * The presence of a '::' will parse as one, two or three zero length
1243 * elements.
1244 */
1245 if (!CONF_parse_list(in, ':', 0, ipv6_cb, &v6stat))
1246 return 0;
1247
1248 /* Now for some sanity checks */
1249
1250 if (v6stat.zero_pos == -1) {
1251 /* If no '::' must have exactly 16 bytes */
1252 if (v6stat.total != 16)
1253 return 0;
1254 } else {
1255 /* If '::' must have less than 16 bytes */
1256 if (v6stat.total == 16)
1257 return 0;
1258 /* More than three zeroes is an error */
1259 if (v6stat.zero_cnt > 3)
1260 return 0;
1261 /* Can only have three zeroes if nothing else present */
1262 else if (v6stat.zero_cnt == 3) {
1263 if (v6stat.total > 0)
1264 return 0;
1265 }
1266 /* Can only have two zeroes if at start or end */
1267 else if (v6stat.zero_cnt == 2) {
1268 if ((v6stat.zero_pos != 0)
1269 && (v6stat.zero_pos != v6stat.total))
1270 return 0;
1271 } else
1272 /* Can only have one zero if *not* start or end */
1273 {
1274 if ((v6stat.zero_pos == 0)
1275 || (v6stat.zero_pos == v6stat.total))
1276 return 0;
1277 }
1278 }
1279
1280 /* Format result */
1281
1282 if (v6stat.zero_pos >= 0) {
1283 /* Copy initial part */
1284 OPENSSL_memcpy(v6, v6stat.tmp, v6stat.zero_pos);
1285 /* Zero middle */
1286 OPENSSL_memset(v6 + v6stat.zero_pos, 0, 16 - v6stat.total);
1287 /* Copy final part */
1288 if (v6stat.total != v6stat.zero_pos)
1289 OPENSSL_memcpy(v6 + v6stat.zero_pos + 16 - v6stat.total,
1290 v6stat.tmp + v6stat.zero_pos,
1291 v6stat.total - v6stat.zero_pos);
1292 } else
1293 OPENSSL_memcpy(v6, v6stat.tmp, 16);
1294
1295 return 1;
1296}
1297
1298static int ipv6_cb(const char *elem, int len, void *usr)
1299{
1300 IPV6_STAT *s = usr;
1301 /* Error if 16 bytes written */
1302 if (s->total == 16)
1303 return 0;
1304 if (len == 0) {
1305 /* Zero length element, corresponds to '::' */
1306 if (s->zero_pos == -1)
1307 s->zero_pos = s->total;
1308 /* If we've already got a :: its an error */
1309 else if (s->zero_pos != s->total)
1310 return 0;
1311 s->zero_cnt++;
1312 } else {
1313 /* If more than 4 characters could be final a.b.c.d form */
1314 if (len > 4) {
1315 /* Need at least 4 bytes left */
1316 if (s->total > 12)
1317 return 0;
1318 /* Must be end of string */
1319 if (elem[len])
1320 return 0;
1321 if (!ipv4_from_asc(s->tmp + s->total, elem))
1322 return 0;
1323 s->total += 4;
1324 } else {
1325 if (!ipv6_hex(s->tmp + s->total, elem, len))
1326 return 0;
1327 s->total += 2;
1328 }
1329 }
1330 return 1;
1331}
1332
1333/*
1334 * Convert a string of up to 4 hex digits into the corresponding IPv6 form.
1335 */
1336
1337static int ipv6_hex(unsigned char *out, const char *in, int inlen)
1338{
1339 unsigned char c;
1340 unsigned int num = 0;
1341 if (inlen > 4)
1342 return 0;
1343 while (inlen--) {
1344 c = *in++;
1345 num <<= 4;
1346 if ((c >= '0') && (c <= '9'))
1347 num |= c - '0';
1348 else if ((c >= 'A') && (c <= 'F'))
1349 num |= c - 'A' + 10;
1350 else if ((c >= 'a') && (c <= 'f'))
1351 num |= c - 'a' + 10;
1352 else
1353 return 0;
1354 }
1355 out[0] = num >> 8;
1356 out[1] = num & 0xff;
1357 return 1;
1358}

1360int X509V3_NAME_from_section(X509_NAME *nm, STACK_OF (CONF_VALUE) * dn_sk,
1361 unsigned long chtype)
1362{
1363 CONF_VALUE *v;
1364 int mval;
1365 size_t i;
1366 char *p, *type;
1367 if (!nm)
1368 return 0;
1369
1370 for (i = 0; i < sk_CONF_VALUE_num(dn_sk); i++) {
1371 v = sk_CONF_VALUE_value(dn_sk, i);
1372 type = v->name;
1373 /*
1374 * Skip past any leading X. X: X, etc to allow for multiple instances
1375 */
1376 for (p = type; *p; p++)
1377 if ((*p == ':') || (*p == ',') || (*p == '.')) {
1378 p++;
1379 if (*p)
1380 type = p;
1381 break;
1382 }
1383 if (*type == '+') {
1384 mval = -1;
1385 type++;
1386 } else
1387 mval = 0;
1388 if (!X509_NAME_add_entry_by_txt(nm, type, chtype,
1389 (unsigned char *)v->value, -1, -1,
1390 mval))
1391 return 0;
1392
1393 }
1394 return 1;
1395}
